{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d72dc185-3660-4333-a309-9beab786159a","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nMTP uses `--filter` but with **different operators**:\n\n| VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|\n| `~` (contains) | `~=` | contains |\n| `&` (and) | `&` | same |\n| `FullyQualifiedName` | `FullyQualifiedName` | same |\n| `Category` | `Category` | same (maps to `Trait`) |\n\nYour new CI command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category~=Smoke\"\n```\n\nOr, if running the test executable directly (MTP native mode):\n\n```bash\n./TestProject --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category~=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### 2. `[Trait]` → xUnit v3 equivalent\n\nYour `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` attribute still works in xUnit v3, so no code changes needed there.\n\n**Key gotcha:** In VSTest `~` meant \"contains\", but MTP requires `~=` for contains. Using bare `~` will silently match nothing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"81fe1389-dfe0-4a24-b652-6e156e8f117b","outputTokens":308,"requestId":"4817:99ACC:32322F8:36CE63D:69FBE403"},"id":"bcc6e450-5b45-4786-92d8-ec4de5092580","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:59:55.316Z","parentId":"815892ba-d078-4614-b2e3-ec66501bb9ac"}
